<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-11-10T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-11-10T19:00:00-05:00" n="369" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d369">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5117: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Munro</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-11-10T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 10,
                                        1927—7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>187. Your 318, November 4, 3 p.m. Department’s 173, October 29, 1 p.m.
                            was sent on recommendation of Minister for Foreign Affairs contained in
                            your 289, October 24, 3 p.m. concurred in by you. In view of change in
                            situation Department has no objection to procedure agreed to by both
                            parties.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>